-- India's Life Insurance to Seek Approval for Infrastructure Bonds, PTI Says
-- B y   M a d e l e n e   P e a r s o n
-- 2010-10-03T05:44:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-03/india-s-life-insurance-to-seek-approval-for-infrastructure-bonds-pti-says.html
Life Insurance Corp. of India, the
nation’s largest insurer, plans to approach the regulator, IRDA,
in the next 8-10 days for approval for floating infrastructure
bonds, Press Trust of India reported, citing an official from
the insurer it didn’t identify.  The official refused to disclose the size of the bond
issue, the report said.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Madelene Pearson in Mumbai at 
